J. B. Rainsberger wrote:

&gt; Well, if the document conforms to an HTML-based DTD, then certainly a
&gt; browser will understand it, except possibly for JavaScript errors.

Sadly, that&#39;s not true...

&lt;html&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
&lt;title/&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
Test
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

The above conforms to the strict xhtml dtd. Try it with the latest IE -
you will see nothing. Only after you replace &lt;title/&gt; by &lt;title&gt;&lt;/title&gt;
it will work.

More of those subtleties are documented at
http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/#guidelines

